Absent: Tom Burch, Jeff Barr, Andrew Owen, Nima Kulkarni, Jeff Donohue, Queenie Averette, Mark Mitchell, Keith Morgan, Mikal Forbush, Al Gentry, David Andrews, Lisa Tanner Norkus

Board of Elections Interviews

Interviews were conducted for the LDP nominations for Board of Elections in Jefferson County. Each candidate was given 3 minutes to provide a personal statement to the EC. Following the candidate interviews, electronic ballots were distributed and EC members were to select up to 5 individuals. The top 5 would be submitted to KY SOS for consideration for BOE.

Candidates with the most votes were:
	•	Brandon Kenney
	•	Kathryn Hargraves
	•	Melinda Townsend-Breslin
	•	Ginger Wallace
	•	Scott Furkin

Bylaws Committee

The Bylaws Committee has completed an update of the LDP bylaws. Bylaws will be presented to the incoming EC following re-org for review and adoption.

Reorganization

Chair Gatti provided an update on registration and nomination progress. LD leaders are expected to identify potential precinct leaders in their districts and share all materials regarding the re-org process.

Precinct Convention nomination and registration portal closes on April 30th. Contested precinct election ballots will be distributed on May 8th and be open until May 10th. County Convention will take place on May 17th at Hartford Hall. State Convention is June 14th in Owensboro.
 
Headquarters Update

The HVAC system in the front half of the building is broken and needs to be replaced. Quotes have been received from 3 companies.

Chair Gatti requested up to $5000 for a replacement HVAC system. Logan Gatti motioned, Beth Thorpe seconded. Approved by voice vote.

Meeting adjourned











