 Chair Report


   ●​ Harvey Sloane Rally Recap- Was a success. We will consider Harvey a resource still. Cheers to
      Meredith for her speech- got feedback from mobilize that rally go-ers were impressed by her.
   ●​ Women Deliver Democracy Luncheon- This is a smaller fundraiser for us, early bird tix end
      August 31st. All Executive Committee members are expected to sell a ticket using their link (Beth
      sent these out in email), selling tickets can contribute to the $500 expectation of individual
      fundraising by Committee members ($500 goal that was set previously through an Executive
      Meeting).
   ●​ NOIR Voter Project- shout out to Robin Foxx. First meeting of the NOIR happened on Sunday. All
      Exec Members are encouraged to create projects like this. Find a weakness in your district and
      build a project for it.
   ●​ Pride Festival Booth- Sept 6th. Small table. Need volunteers. 4 to 5 hours in duration.
   ●​ Precinct Vacancies- Shout out to district 34 for finding new precinct leaders. If you find someone
      to fill a precinct role, you need to confirm with the precinct vacancy document that is in the
      portal. If there is a vacancy, you must confirm they are a registered Dem and reside in your
      district. If that information is correct, we can approve them. We will vote on them as an exec
      committee. That info needs to be emailed to Logan Gatti before the Exec Committee meeting so
      that the voting can be on the agenda.
   ●​ Committee Member Expectations- we must be organizing our districts and outreaching to
      people. In Q4, we will start to ask people to submit what they have done.
   ●​ Trying to establish extra communication time at the end of Exec meetings. Want the last 15
      minutes to be for conversations and collaboration between members. “Shared learning
      sessions”.

PRECINCT LEADER NOMINATIONS
34th District- Michael Price, Moved Janice Dean, 2nd by Max Morley, No opposition
35th District- Whitney England, Moved- Carolyn Benedict, seconded by Beth Thorpe, No opposition


