chair. Dem caucus discussed 2026 electoral plan. We should be on offense for 2026. Pickup
districts 11, 19, 23. They are non-partisan so that makes it more challenging. 3 state house
districts without a candidate: 37, 33, 36.
Senate: 36th. Deadline closes on January. 5. Metro spots open 11, 19, 23, 13, 25

Finance:
report on shared drive
Volunteers:
Successful canvassing in 34th.
Ongoing Mitch protests.
Postcarding continues- Focusing on Cali Prop 50

Endorsement process committee:
Brand new process, want to have it ready and presented by the Oct meeting. Looking for
comments, then will take that feedback and bring it back for review in Nov, then finalize in Dec.
Looking to do it in the most fair way possible. There have been complaints about subjectivity in
the past. We are trying to be as objective as possible in this process. Anyone can join this
committee. Logan is the committee chair.
 Open issues

   ❖​ EC Portal -
          ➢​ Beth needs to know if people are getting the LouDem emails. Encouraged to put our
               main email contacts in your addresses so they don’t go into spam.
          ➢​ Beth gave a quick tutorial of the online portal.
          ➢​ Must use 2 factor identification, worry about your password. You could be a target.
          ➢​ Explore the folders on the portal. LD folders are there. Open seats are on file there. KDP
               resources. Read the guide if you are lost in the party objectives and procedures. If you
               think something should be on there, tell Beth.
          ➢​ Looking for 8 people to experiment with Discord. Discord will eventually house Forums
               for committees and LDs. This will help to stop endless emails and texts.
          ➢​ Information on why and how to use Mobilize for your LD events. Need to submit them 2
               to 3 weeks ahead of time before event. Allows Beth to put it on socials.
          ➢​ How to not get your emails get put into junk files when sending emails out to your
               district- started this train of thought but didn’t go into it before we started talking about
               something else
   ❖​ Beth offered info cards to pass out for canvassing
   ❖​ Thinking of doing a quick training on canvassing next meeting? Breakout rooms online or in
      person? Still debating on process.
   ❖​ Tony Hardin will be the main votebuilder person for the district. Ask him for guidance.
   ❖​ Friday Noble Funk Young Dems event.
   ❖​ Beth is sharing things via Google Drive- Beth needs everyone to have a Google email so you can
      access the documents.

