Endorsement vote for Mayor. Shamika Parrish-Wright vs Craig Greenberg. Rules stipulate that we, as a body, must do an initial vote on if we will vote to make an endorsement at all. This is a hand-count vote. No proxies. Zoom voting permitted.
Actual endorsement vote is electronic. Secret voting. No proxies. Zoom voting permitted. 3 options: Parrish-Wright/Greenberg/Abstain. 60% must be reached by a candidate for endorsement. A second vote will be given if no candidate reaches 60%. After second vote, if 60% is not reached, voting stops and no endorsement is given. 
Motion to proceed with endorsement. 
Motion: John Stovall
                   Seconded:Max Morley

                   Motion passed, no nays
 
Results: Greenberg- 69%, Parrish-Wright- 27%, Abstain- 4%
Greenberg given LDP endorsement. 

Overview of what this means:
LDP is endorsing Mayor Greenberg. Secret ballots are secret for a reason. The voting tally results (number of votes) should not go out to the public. The press release will go out tonight. 
